entry.name: A search for protein biomarkers links olfactory signal transduction to social immunity
entry.description: We have looked across different honey bee colonies, multiple generations and multiple genetic backgrounds to identify protein expression patterns correlated with hygienic behaviour

additional_fields.field: All samples were honey bee worker antennae. Tissues were pulverized in a bead mill and protein was extracted and digested in solution with trypsin. Peptide samples were dimethylated in triplex for quantitation
All data processing was done using MSQuant. Quantitation and search results from MSQ are provided

Guarna M, Melathopoulos AP, Huxter E, Iovinella I, Parker R, Stoynov N, Tam A, Moon KM, Chan Q, Pelosi P, White R, Pernal SF, Foster LJ. A search for protein biomarkers links olfactory signal transduction to social immunity. BMC Genomics. 2015 Feb 8;16(1):63
Centre for High-Throughput Biology, University of British Columbia
